  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary objective of this study is to test whether a fluid resuscitation protocol guided
      by non-invasive hemodynamic measures reduces the progression of organ dysfunction (defined by
      an increase in the Serial Organ Failure Assessment Score ≥ 1 over the first 72 hours) in
      sepsis patients presenting to the Emergency Department without evidence of shock.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
